VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT badCertificateCallback\s*:\s*\([^)]*\)\s*(?:=>|\{)[^}]*(?:=>|return)\s*true
WHEN EXPR MISSING:test|development|localhost|staging|certificate pinning
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects Dio HttpClient configurations that accept all TLS certificates via badCertificateCallback returning true.
TRACE Externalized mobile rule logic for Bad Certificate Callback Accepting All Certificates.
